channel.description:
[center][size=36pt]Hi,[/size][/center]
I am Arham 4 and am here to give you a custom quest called "The Monky Rescue". It's a very simple quest but it teaches you dialogue very well. Before we start you should do [url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,558960.0.html]this[/url] or you'll get errors and will have to convert about 170 dialogues. Your choice :).

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=laVV7K3qRDw

[hr]
[center][size=24pt]What's this quest?[/size][/center]
[center]
[left][size=36pt]"[/size][/left] In your local village, you find the towns High Priest worried. When going up to him, you make him angry, but you know he really needs you. So you go and try to find a way to arrange 500 coins. Why do you set off and get 500 coins you ask? Because there is a kidnapper involved in this story, who took the High Priests son. In the midst of the action, you gain the High Priests trust from the 500 coins you arranged for him. You are then asked to do the hard task of retrieving the High Priest's son, and from the ladder down comes wacky places. At one point, you go to Lumbridge, wait no, Varrock, wait no, Trollheim, wait no, THE KIDNAPPERS LAIR!!!! Can you rescue the High Priest's son, or will you die before doing so? [right][size=36pt]"[/size][/right][/center]

[hr]

Interesting right? Well, lets start programming this to your server!

[hr]

To start off, open [b]package org.randqm.model.player[/b] and open DialogueHandler. Inside, search for

[code=java]
public void startDialogue (int npcId) {
[/code]

Below

[code=java]
		switch(npcId) {
[/code]

Add

[code=java]
		case 1986:
			if (c.monkyRescue == 0) {
				dia(23);
			} else if (c.monkyRescue == 1) {
				dia(57);
			} else if (c.monkyRescue == 2) {
				dia(97);
			} else if (c.monkyRescue == 3) {
				dia(138);
			} else if (c.monkyRescue == 4) {
				dia(160);
			}
		break;
		case 373:
			if (c.monkyRescue == 1) {
				dia(58);
			} else if (c.monkyRescue == 2) {
				dia(92);
			} else if (c.monkyRescue == 4) {
				dia(141);
			} else if (c.monkyRescue == 3) {
				dia(163);
			}
		break;
		case 651:
				dia(54);
			if (c.monkyRescue == 1 || c.monkyRescue == 2) {
				int randomDialogue = Misc.random(2);
				switch (randomDialogue) {
				case 0:
					dia(55);
				break;
				case 1:
					dia(56);
				break;
				}
			}
			break;
		case 802:
			if(c.monkyRescue == 3) {
				dia(140);
			} else if (c.monkyRescue == 4) {
				dia(161);
			}
		break;
		case 2476:
			if(c.monkyRescue == 3) {
				dia(141);
			}
		break;
[/code]

What we just did was make the server know what to do to the npcs in certain times.

